President Trump and Prime Minister Modi of India held a meeting during the G7 summit in France. They discussed various topics including trade, military, and bilateral issues between India and Pakistan. Trump expressed his belief that Modi has the situation in Kashmir under control and that India and Pakistan should work together to fight poverty, illiteracy, and disease. When asked about the ongoing trade war with China, Trump mentioned that there have been high-level communications and expressed his hope for a resolution. He also mentioned the recent trade deal with Japan and the progress in negotiations with the European Union. Trump praised the unity among the G7 nations and highlighted his good relationships with world leaders. He also mentioned his willingness to include Russia in future G7 meetings.